{"uri":"oai:oa.upm.es:31185","url":"file:///Users/cbadenes/Temp/ressist-resources/corpus/oaipmh/4ee0f426-6074-46bf-a6ef-4fe22a4f3cd4.pdf","source":{"name":"oa.upm.es","uri":"http://www.epnoi.org/oaipmh/oa.upm.es/cgi/oai2","url":"http://oa.upm.es/cgi/oai2","protocol":"oaipmh"},"metainformation":{"title":"Experimental implementation of a biometric laser synaptic sensor","published":"2015-04-11T11:57:46Z","format":"pdf","language":"eng","rights":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0/es/","description":"We fabricate a biometric laser fiber synaptic sensor to transmit information from one neuron cell to the other by an optical way. The optical synapse is constructed on the base of an erbium-doped fiber laser, whose pumped diode current is driven by a pre-synaptic FitzHugh–Nagumo electronic neuron, and the laser output controls a post-synaptic FitzHugh–Nagumo electronic neuron. The implemented laser synapse displays very rich dynamics, including fixed points, periodic orbits with different frequency-locking ratios and chaos. These regimes can be beneficial for efficient biorobotics, where behavioral flexibility subserved by synaptic connectivity is a challenge.","creators":[{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Pisarchik-Alexander%20N.","name":"Alexander N.","surname":"Pisarchik"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Sevilla-Escoboza-Ricardo","name":"Ricardo","surname":"Sevilla-Escoboza"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Jaimes-Reategui-Rider","name":"Rider","surname":"Jaimes-Reategui"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Huerta%20Cuellar-Guillermo","name":"Guillermo","surname":"Huerta Cuellar"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Garc%C3%ADa%20L%C3%B3pez-J.%20Hugo","name":"J. Hugo","surname":"García López"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Kazantsev-Victor%20B.","name":"Victor B.","surname":"Kazantsev"}]},"bagOfWords":["neuron","laser","synaps","frequenc","synapt","figur","signal","sensor","electron","control","art